<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 17 at 4:22PM CDT  by NWS QuadCities</headline>
<description>...Burst of Heavier Snow This Afternoon...
Doppler radar indicated bursts of moderate to heavy snowfall are
moving into much of southeast Iowa and west central Illinois. Due
to the rapid rate of snowfall there may be a quick inch or two of
slushy snow, mainly on elevated and grassy areas.
The main impact will be greatly reduced visibility to less than a
mile in the heavier snowfall.
While roads should remain wet you should use extra caution while
driving due to the low visibility.</description>
